\[\frac{1}{2}\left[f\left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right) + g\left(\frac{3}{4}\right)\right]\left(\frac{3}{4} - \frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right).\]
We have
\begin{align*}
f\left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right) &= \left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right)^2 + \frac{5}{12}, \\
g\left(\frac{3}{4}\right) &= 2\left(1 - \frac{4\cdot\frac{3}{4}}{3}\right) = \frac{1}{2},
\end{align*}
so the area of the right half is
\[\frac{1}{2}\left[\left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right)^2 + \frac{5}{12} + \frac{1}{2}\right]\left(\frac{3}{4} - \frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right).\]
Thus, the area of the entire region is
\begin{align*}
\alpha &= \left[\left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right)^2 + \frac{5}{12} + \frac{1}{2}\right]\left(\frac{3}{4} - \frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right) \\
&= \left[\left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right)^2 + \frac{17}{12}\right]\left(\frac{15}{4} - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}\right).
\end{align*}
Finally, we compute $9\alpha$:
\begin{align*}
9\alpha &= 9\left[\left(\frac{8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}}{2}\right)^2 + \frac{17}{12}\right]\left(\frac{15}{4} - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}\right) \\
&= \left[\left(8 - \sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}\right)^2 + \frac{17}{4}\right]\left(15 - 4\sqrt{\frac{220}{3}}\right) \\
&= \boxed{021}.
\end{align*}

We can rewrite the sum $S$ as follows:
